WEBVTT

01:11.863 --> 01:13.490
My name is Tom Sims.

01:14.283 --> 01:15.742
I'm a newspaper columnist.

01:17.327 --> 01:19.413
Several years ago I covered firsthand

01:19.663 --> 01:24.001
the incredible story you are about to see
re-created in this motion picture.

01:25.335 --> 01:29.131
It is a human horror story
of ghastly proportions and ...

01:30.090 --> 01:32.301
...profound reverberations.

01:33.802 --> 01:36.972
But because it is human,
perhaps we can learn something from it.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.600
Something of ourselves ...

01:40.309 --> 01:42.394
...of our own fears and needs.

01:43.186 --> 01:45.731
But please, let me warn you ...

01:46.982 --> 01:50.152
The events have been
re-created in detail.

01:51.403 --> 01:53.655
Nothing has been left
to the imagination.

01:54.031 --> 01:56.533
It is not a story
for the squeamish ...

01:56.992 --> 01:58.952
...or the faint-hearted.

02:00.829 --> 02:03.957
Now that you stand warned,
we can proceed with our story.

02:05.292 --> 02:07.544
It is the story of Ezra Cobb:

02:07.753 --> 02:10.213
murderer, grave robber, ...

02:11.340 --> 02:12.924
...necrophiliac perhaps, ...

02:13.717 --> 02:17.179
...or, as you may remember him
from those stories of long ago,

02:17.846 --> 02:19.473
...the Butcher of Woodside.

02:29.316 --> 02:31.485
'When Ez was 10,
his father died.

02:31.652 --> 02:33.362
'For the next 15 years,

02:33.362 --> 02:35.739
'Ez and his mother worked
the farm by themselves,

02:35.906 --> 02:39.159
'growing more dependent on each other
with the passage of time.

02:39.368 --> 02:41.787
'Then Amanda Cobb suffered
a paralysing stroke

02:41.787 --> 02:43.789
'which crippled her body
from the waist down

02:43.789 --> 02:45.374
'and left her bedridden.

02:45.540 --> 02:47.125
'Ez brought her downstairs,

02:47.125 --> 02:50.295
'sealing off the upstairs room,
so he could be closer to her.

02:50.504 --> 02:53.090
'For 12 years,
he slept outside her door,

02:53.256 --> 02:56.343
'waiting on her, feeding her,
bathing her,

02:56.510 --> 02:58.845
'reading to her, comforting her.

02:59.888 --> 03:02.683
'To his neighbours,
he was a devoted son.

03:03.600 --> 03:07.062
'But that devotion masked
a growing psychosis

03:07.437 --> 03:10.440
'which came to the surface
when his mother died.'

03:21.201 --> 03:22.202
Mama?

03:24.121 --> 03:25.455
Brought you some soup, Mama.

03:26.748 --> 03:27.916
It's good and hot today.

03:39.010 --> 03:40.053
Ez?

03:42.889 --> 03:44.057
Take my hand.

03:47.018 --> 03:48.812
Are you holding my hand?

03:49.730 --> 03:51.605
Yes.

03:51.606 --> 03:53.024
I can't feel you.

03:54.568 --> 03:57.904
Cold. Must be ... draughts.

04:07.289 --> 04:09.791
Just got to get the circulation
going again, that's all.

04:09.958 --> 04:12.961
So it's to be now, then, is it?

04:15.505 --> 04:17.841
I can't see you too clearly, Ez.

04:18.008 --> 04:19.301
You look blurred.

04:19.760 --> 04:22.095
You're ... you're tired, Mama, is all.

04:22.387 --> 04:24.973
- Here, I brought you some soup.
- No.

04:25.140 --> 04:26.600
- Good and hot.
- No.

04:26.892 --> 04:29.519
I'm not tired,
and I don't want no soup.

04:30.479 --> 04:32.189
- I'm dying.
- No, Mama.

04:32.397 --> 04:34.274
I'm dying,
and that's all there is to it.

04:34.441 --> 04:37.152
No'm. You just need
some rest is all.

04:37.360 --> 04:38.779
Now, you be quiet
and listen to me.

04:38.945 --> 04:42.532
If I go into a coma,
don't take me to no hospital.

04:42.741 --> 04:46.077
I want to die in my own bed,
my own room, ...

04:46.661 --> 04:47.954
...with you here.

04:48.538 --> 04:51.958
If you need any help later,
after I'm gone, ...

04:52.459 --> 04:55.378
...call Maureen Selby.

04:56.087 --> 04:59.966
Say it now, Ez. Maureen Selby.

05:00.175 --> 05:01.176
Mau...

05:01.802 --> 05:04.221
Maureen ... Selby.

05:04.888 --> 05:07.057
Maureen's the only woman
I ever did trust.

05:07.557 --> 05:10.101
She's fat, that's why. A big heifer.

05:10.560 --> 05:12.771
But she's the only
good-hearted woman I ever knew.

05:14.147 --> 05:15.565
As for the rest of them, ...

05:16.024 --> 05:20.362
...they're a lot of filthy,
black-souled sluts

05:20.529 --> 05:22.405
with pus-filled sores that ...

05:24.533 --> 05:26.116
Ez?

05:26.117 --> 05:27.118
Ez ...

05:28.537 --> 05:29.538
I ...

05:29.788 --> 05:33.375
I... I c-can't br-breathe.

05:33.750 --> 05:36.378
You're gonna be all right.

05:36.837 --> 05:40.090
You just need ...
something to eat, that's all.

05:40.465 --> 05:41.508
Honest!

05:41.925 --> 05:45.178
I know I'm ...
I'm leaving you now.

05:46.263 --> 05:47.681
And that's for certain.

05:48.640 --> 05:51.768
I don't want to leave
worrying about you.

05:52.894 --> 05:57.482
Oh, you're such
a babe in the woods, a child.

05:58.650 --> 06:00.694
I sheltered you too much, I guess.

06:02.362 --> 06:05.115
But I just know
some money-stealing bitch

06:05.282 --> 06:08.410
is gonna come along
and try to take advantage of you.

06:10.620 --> 06:12.289
Remember what I've always told you.

06:12.747 --> 06:16.668
The wages of sin is gonorrhoea,
syphilis and death!

06:17.168 --> 06:22.299
They'll use their bodies to ...
to steal from you.

06:22.841 --> 06:25.468
They'll steal your life and your soul.

06:27.512 --> 06:29.139
Leave 'em alone.

06:29.890 --> 06:32.767
Most of 'em are filled
with diseases that tick.

06:35.979 --> 06:37.689
God will wash them away ...

06:38.899 --> 06:41.401
...like he did in the time of Noah.

06:43.737 --> 06:48.158
God looked upon the earth,
and behold, it was corrupt, ...

06:49.576 --> 06:53.204
...for all flesh had corrupted
his way upon the earth.

06:54.539 --> 06:56.374
Then God said unto Noah, ...

06:57.375 --> 07:00.545
"The end of all flesh
is come before me."

07:02.589 --> 07:04.966
Do you know what God
did then, Ez?

07:05.550 --> 07:07.886
Yes'm. The flood.

07:09.012 --> 07:12.140
Yes, sir ... the flood.

07:13.141 --> 07:16.394
Oh, I wish I could
be here to see it.

07:18.730 --> 07:21.399
You're still a handsome
young man, Ez.

07:22.567 --> 07:25.320
You'll have great attraction
for the opposite sex.

07:27.447 --> 07:31.660
That's why you gotta be so careful.

07:33.495 --> 07:37.040
Oh, Ez ... it hurts.

07:38.708 --> 07:39.876
Hurts.

07:40.669 --> 07:42.628
Eat.

07:42.629 --> 07:44.839
You'll be all right, honest.

07:51.513 --> 07:54.432
No, you won't die, honest.

07:59.396 --> 08:00.563
Please, Mama.

08:00.730 --> 08:02.816
Please, Mama, don't leave me.

08:06.945 --> 08:08.738
Mama, no, please.

08:08.947 --> 08:11.408
No, please. No.

08:14.035 --> 08:15.745
Mama, Mama.

08:17.205 --> 08:18.623
Mama ...

09:27.567 --> 09:29.277
How you holding up, Ez?

09:32.572 --> 09:34.449
We're so sorry, Ez.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.543
She was a great lady, Ez.

09:46.586 --> 09:48.088
Real ...

09:50.340 --> 09:51.925
Real demure.

09:57.013 --> 09:58.973
Real religious.

10:05.396 --> 10:07.732
The boys wanted to come, Ez, but ...

10:07.941 --> 10:10.610
Well, I didn't think they should.

10:10.777 --> 10:13.571
But they do send
their condolences, though.

10:21.496 --> 10:23.456
She looks nice, Ez.

10:24.666 --> 10:26.501
Real natural.

10:29.254 --> 10:31.464
You'd think
she was just sleeping.

10:36.511 --> 10:38.054
She is.

10:43.017 --> 10:44.602
That's all it is.

10:48.481 --> 10:49.983
Just sleep.

11:13.214 --> 11:16.467
A month passed.
Six months. A year.

11:17.343 --> 11:20.096
Still Ezra refused to accept
the death of his mother.

11:21.055 --> 11:24.309
He visited her grave
as often as four or five times a week.

11:25.268 --> 11:27.561
And at home ...

11:27.562 --> 11:30.315
'At home he continued
as though she were only away on a trip.

11:31.065 --> 11:32.692
'He kept her room neat and clean

11:32.859 --> 11:34.569
'and made sure
the stove was always going,

11:34.569 --> 11:36.738
'so it would be warm
when she returned to him.

11:37.780 --> 11:39.073
'He dreamed about her,

11:39.657 --> 11:42.243
'and in his despair
even wrote letters to her.

11:44.454 --> 11:48.750
'To the outside world,
Ez was, oh, a little eccentric maybe,

11:48.750 --> 11:50.877
'but basically a normal, decent guy.

11:51.544 --> 11:52.962
'He quit farming altogether

11:53.129 --> 11:55.965
'and hired on as a general
handyman for his neighbours

11:56.132 --> 11:58.426
'and especially his good friend
Harlan Kootz.'

11:58.593 --> 12:01.596
Bobby, come on.
It's time to go.

12:01.763 --> 12:02.847
OK, Mum.

12:04.140 --> 12:05.307
Bye.

12:05.308 --> 12:08.645
'But the loneliness within him
had grown to a vast abyss,

12:08.811 --> 12:12.190
'and the pain of his loss at last
pushed him over the precipice

12:12.357 --> 12:13.524
'and into madness.'

12:13.691 --> 12:15.151
Mama ...

12:18.196 --> 12:20.323
...when you comin' home again?

12:27.622 --> 12:29.749
I'm real lonesome, Mama.

12:32.126 --> 12:38.049
There's nothing
but snow and snow and snow.

12:39.509 --> 12:42.845
And the wind blowing
and blowing and blowing.

12:44.764 --> 12:46.641
And it's so cold.

12:48.768 --> 12:51.729
And I miss you with all my heart.

12:53.690 --> 12:55.275
Amen.

13:00.530 --> 13:04.701
'If you miss me so much,
why don't you come and bring me home?'

13:06.369 --> 13:07.537
Mama?

13:09.956 --> 13:12.333
'You should be
ashamed of yourself, ...

13:12.917 --> 13:16.713
...'leaving me here
more than a year now.

13:17.714 --> 13:21.050
'I'm all alone
here in the dark.

13:21.259 --> 13:22.885
'Shame, Ez!'

13:24.679 --> 13:27.974
Mama, I wrote to you.

13:29.976 --> 13:32.145
'Don't get no letters here.

13:33.896 --> 13:36.899
'Now, why don't you come
and bring me home?

13:38.401 --> 13:39.944
'Bring me home ...

13:40.987 --> 13:42.530
'Bring me home ...'

13:45.616 --> 13:47.910
I'm comin', Mama!

13:48.953 --> 13:50.705
'And so he went
to bring her home.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.433
'Perhaps, in his twisted mind

14:10.600 --> 14:13.895
'he imagined she would look
the way she had in life.'

14:27.617 --> 14:29.911
Mama. Mama.

15:04.487 --> 15:06.364
I'm takin' you home, Mama.

15:08.157 --> 15:09.700
Home.

15:14.497 --> 15:17.834
♪ She's the girl of my dreams ♪

15:18.000 --> 15:21.129
♪ And her fair face beams ♪

15:21.129 --> 15:25.299
♪ She's the sweetheart ♪
♪ of Sigma Chi ... ♪

15:56.581 --> 15:59.667
What in the hell
do you think you're doing, Ez?

15:59.876 --> 16:02.712
N-nothin', sir.
What do you mean?

16:02.920 --> 16:05.298
Oh, come on.
You know what I mean.

16:07.925 --> 16:09.677
Well, she wanted
to come home, Sheriff.

16:10.553 --> 16:13.139
- She told me she did. Otherwise I...
- Now, look, look, look.

16:13.306 --> 16:15.683
This is a 35-mile-an-hour zone,

16:15.850 --> 16:18.728
and you were going 50
if you were going anything.

16:18.895 --> 16:20.646
Now, let me smell your breath.

16:21.606 --> 16:25.651
Good God!
What in the hell is that?

16:26.360 --> 16:29.697
What have you been drinkin', Ez?
Goddamn!

16:31.657 --> 16:35.745
Nothin', sir, er...
It's just a hog I butchered is all.

16:35.912 --> 16:39.874
Er... I forgot to take it out of the truck.
It kind of got to smellin'.

16:40.041 --> 16:42.960
Jesus Christ, you ain't kiddin'!

16:46.297 --> 16:50.092
I'm gonna let you go this time, Ez,
but don't let it happen again, you hear?

16:51.469 --> 16:55.306
And for Christ's sake,
bury that, will you?

16:55.473 --> 16:56.599
Yes, sir.

16:57.391 --> 17:00.102
I sure will ... er, first thing.

17:00.686 --> 17:02.480
No more speeding, you hear?

17:02.647 --> 17:03.648
Yes, sir.

17:04.440 --> 17:05.483
I mean, no, sir.

17:06.275 --> 17:17.369
All right.

17:17.370 --> 17:20.540
I apologise for calling you
a hog, Mama.

17:26.212 --> 17:27.797
Get you in bed.

17:28.923 --> 17:30.925
You need to lie back down.

17:32.635 --> 17:34.011
Fix you up.

17:34.178 --> 17:37.223
You won't even
know yourself, honest.

17:41.018 --> 17:42.645
See your room?

17:44.230 --> 17:45.356
Just like it used to be.

18:07.962 --> 18:09.547
Oh, Mama.

18:11.340 --> 18:13.175
You're in terrible shape.

18:21.684 --> 18:24.061
Gonna have to put you
back together

18:24.228 --> 18:26.897
like that old egg in the fairy story.

18:32.737 --> 18:35.031
I'm glad you're home.

18:42.872 --> 18:44.332
Here's your Bible.

18:52.840 --> 18:54.383
Your bell.

19:02.683 --> 19:03.851
So he brought her home.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.145
And what now?

19:07.563 --> 19:09.607
Now he intended to restore her.

19:10.733 --> 19:13.402
And to that purpose
he began reading everything he could

19:13.569 --> 19:16.489
about embalming ... taxidermy.

19:17.657 --> 19:19.075
But it wasn't an easy job.

19:19.867 --> 19:22.370
His mother had been buried
for over a year now.

19:22.995 --> 19:24.664
There were lots of repairs to make.

19:25.373 --> 19:27.875
He tried to patch her
with fish skin, with wax,

19:28.042 --> 19:32.129
with any substance which he thought
resembled human flesh.

19:34.340 --> 19:35.675
It wasn't until later

19:36.133 --> 19:38.260
that the idea of using
real flesh occurred to him.

19:41.555 --> 19:44.016
'Ironically enough,
it was his friend and neighbour

19:44.016 --> 19:45.851
'who accidentally gave him
the inspiration.'

19:46.560 --> 19:48.813
God is great, God is good,

19:48.979 --> 19:51.023
let us thank him for this food.

19:51.023 --> 19:52.149
Amen.

19:52.692 --> 19:56.445
Oh, and please take good care
of old Miss Johnson.

19:58.197 --> 19:59.949
Pass the bread to Ezra,
will you, Brad?

20:00.116 --> 20:01.575
What's the matter
with old Miss Johnson?

20:01.742 --> 20:02.827
She kicked the bucket.

20:03.035 --> 20:05.496
She didn't kick the bucket.
She passed away.

20:05.496 --> 20:07.957
My Miss Johnson?
My old Sunday School teacher?

20:08.165 --> 20:10.668
- The very same one.
- I don't believe that.

20:10.668 --> 20:13.546
It's right here in today's paper.
Here it is.

20:13.713 --> 20:15.131
The funeral was this afternoon.

20:16.841 --> 20:19.009
That lady taught me
all through Sunday School

20:19.176 --> 20:20.720
and in the sixth grade.

20:22.054 --> 20:23.472
Taught Ez, too.

20:23.639 --> 20:25.683
Remember that, Ez,
back in sixth grade?

20:25.850 --> 20:27.226
Used to call her
"old flannel face".

20:28.060 --> 20:30.229
- Remember that, Ez?
- No, sir.

20:31.605 --> 20:33.065
Yeah, that's her, all right.

20:34.984 --> 20:36.068
Here. Remember her, Ez?

20:37.695 --> 20:40.239
Oh, that's ...
that's old Miss Johnson there.

20:41.240 --> 20:42.575
What's she doing
in the newspaper?

20:43.242 --> 20:45.202
Dang it, Ez,
I just told you she's dead.

20:45.995 --> 20:49.248
You mean they put her in the paper
just 'cause she's dead?

20:51.959 --> 20:54.253
What's the matter with you, Ez?
That's her danged obituary.

20:55.796 --> 20:56.797
Her what?

20:57.840 --> 21:00.050
Don't tell me you don't know
what's an obituary.

21:03.012 --> 21:04.930
If that don't beat all.

21:04.930 --> 21:07.600
Well, look, when a body dies,
they take all the information

21:07.767 --> 21:10.728
and they put it in the newspaper
in the obituary section.

21:10.895 --> 21:12.354
It tells when the funeral is

21:12.521 --> 21:14.857
and where they're being buried
and all that kind of stuff.

21:15.232 --> 21:16.525
You mean I can find out ...

21:17.443 --> 21:19.320
...where and when
somebody's been buried ...

21:20.154 --> 21:21.530
...on the very same day?

21:22.865 --> 21:25.785
Light at the end of the tunnel,
all right, yes, siree.

21:25.951 --> 21:26.952
You're right, Ez.

21:27.745 --> 21:28.871
Well, I'm gonna look into that.

21:29.872 --> 21:31.957
I'd rather read
the sports section, myself.

21:32.333 --> 21:35.795
Not me. This here could be
real valuable information.

21:36.086 --> 21:39.089
Why? What are you planning to do?
Dig 'em up or something?

21:39.256 --> 21:42.510
No, sir.
Wouldn't have to dig it all up.

21:44.386 --> 21:45.971
Well, I'm sure glad to hear that.

21:46.597 --> 21:49.475
Sure. Why dig it all up
when you can take the parts you need?

21:49.642 --> 21:51.393
Sure, maybe like ...

21:52.770 --> 21:55.481
...like if you needed the head
for repairs or something,

21:55.898 --> 21:57.775
...well, then, just take the head.

22:01.403 --> 22:04.323
Oh, Ez, you're a crazy S.O.B.

22:09.370 --> 22:11.956
Hi, Miss Johnson. Remember me?

22:12.665 --> 22:14.583
I used to be in your
Sunday School class.

22:27.805 --> 22:31.141
There she comes now, real easy.

22:34.895 --> 22:38.774
Next thing to do is get this hair off.

23:40.961 --> 23:42.296
See, Mama?

23:42.296 --> 23:45.132
All I got to do is stitch it on you.

23:54.516 --> 23:55.893
Look, Mama.

23:56.852 --> 23:58.395
I brought you a visitor.

24:13.327 --> 24:16.664
Shh. Don't stay too long, now.

24:23.879 --> 24:26.840
Bet you two ladies have
a lot to talk about.

24:32.346 --> 24:34.723
After that, Ezra made
many visits to the graveyard,

24:34.890 --> 24:38.185
bringing home bodies,
or parts of bodies, ...

24:39.436 --> 24:41.188
...to keep his mother
and himself company.

24:42.481 --> 24:46.694
He was a ghoul, a necromaniac,
a defiler of the dead, ...

24:48.028 --> 24:50.948
...but he had not yet turned
his sickness on a living victim.

24:52.783 --> 24:55.244
It was only a matter of time
until he did.

24:55.786 --> 24:58.831
We're gonna have to take those plugs out,
and take 'em into town -

24:58.831 --> 25:00.874
either get 'em cleaned
or get new ones.

25:15.472 --> 25:17.141
- Ez?
- Sir?

25:18.100 --> 25:21.937
Er, me and Mother,
we've been talking and, er...

25:23.939 --> 25:25.733
Well, we've been thinking that...

25:26.984 --> 25:28.235
Sir?

25:28.902 --> 25:31.113
Well, dang it all, first off,
stop callin' me "sir".

25:31.280 --> 25:32.573
You're as old as I am.

25:32.906 --> 25:35.492
And secondly,
stop callin' Jenny "ma'am".

25:35.492 --> 25:37.077
You're a growed man, Ez.

25:37.828 --> 25:40.873
That's what I want...
wanted. to talk to you about.

25:41.040 --> 25:43.667
I wanted to talk to you
man to man.

25:45.210 --> 25:48.714
See, we're... well, Jenny and me,
we're worried about you,

25:48.922 --> 25:51.050
living up in that old house
there all by yourself,

25:51.216 --> 25:55.512
and, er, we just thought that...
well, we...

25:56.930 --> 25:58.682
Dang it, Jennifer says
you should be married,

25:58.849 --> 26:01.310
and that's what she says
and that's that, so...

26:01.810 --> 26:04.188
Ezra, what my husband
means is that ...

26:04.730 --> 26:06.899
Well, we're just kind of worried
about you, that's all,

26:07.066 --> 26:10.527
and, well, we thought it would be nice
if you could meet someone,

26:10.694 --> 26:12.946
and I'd be glad to introduce you
if you wanted,

26:13.113 --> 26:17.659
you know, someone nice who could be
a companion for you, that's all.

26:18.452 --> 26:20.454
Nope. No'm.

26:22.414 --> 26:23.499
I don't trust 'em.

26:24.374 --> 26:25.876
You don't trust who, Ez?

26:26.376 --> 26:29.797
You know... girls and stuff.

26:30.631 --> 26:31.964
Damn right.

26:31.965 --> 26:34.093
