59:27.397 --> 59:28.440
That's a belly drum.

59:35.989 --> 59:39.659
I'm just trying to show you
I got talents, too.

59:41.369 --> 59:44.414
I may not be handsome like some of them
other fellows you meet up there, but...

59:49.503 --> 59:52.923
You know, 10:1 says you'll feel
a lot better if you eat something.

59:53.465 --> 59:56.343
I would eat, but I can't.

59:57.719 --> 1:00:00.055
- How come?
- My hands.

1:00:00.972 --> 1:00:03.724
Oh.

1:00:03.725 --> 1:00:06.436
That's true, ain't it?

1:00:08.688 --> 1:00:16.279
But... but if I untie you,
you'll... you'll try something.

1:00:16.279 --> 1:00:18.115
No, I won't.

1:00:20.283 --> 1:00:21.368
I promise.

1:00:21.952 --> 1:00:22.953
Well ...

1:00:26.790 --> 1:00:31.920
Ez, that's not a very nice way
to treat your bride, is it?

1:00:33.088 --> 1:00:34.381
Ez, is it?

1:00:35.966 --> 1:00:36.967
Gosh.

1:00:39.344 --> 1:00:42.264
No, it sure ain't.

1:01:08.957 --> 1:01:10.333
I really love you, Mary.

1:01:12.836 --> 1:01:14.171
I love you, too, Ez.

1:01:15.672 --> 1:01:19.759
I knew you did.
I knew deep down you did.

1:01:21.094 --> 1:01:22.679
I'll do everything.

1:01:24.306 --> 1:01:27.017
You just ... just rest.

1:01:28.018 --> 1:01:29.644
Just sleep.

1:01:34.816 --> 1:01:37.027
Call me when you want something.

1:01:47.871 --> 1:01:50.832
You'll always ... be protected.

1:01:54.794 --> 1:01:57.214
I'll put you on a pedestal.

1:01:57.214 --> 1:02:01.968
Hurry, Ez. Ez, untie my hands,
so I can touch you, too.

1:02:20.487 --> 1:02:22.072
Mary.

1:02:55.105 --> 1:02:56.106
No.

1:02:59.609 --> 1:03:01.361
No!

1:03:03.530 --> 1:03:04.948
No!

1:03:06.366 --> 1:03:08.535
Mama! Mama!

1:03:57.125 --> 1:03:58.835
'The only clue left to the police

1:03:59.002 --> 1:04:00.879
'in the disappearance
of Mary Ransom

1:04:00.879 --> 1:04:04.090
'was her parked car
with the two rear tyres slashed.

1:04:04.090 --> 1:04:06.843
'Hardly astonishing, then,
that no one ever thought of Ezra Cobb

1:04:07.010 --> 1:04:09.763
'as a suspect
in the barmaid's disappearance.

1:04:09.929 --> 1:04:11.598
'If only they had.'

1:04:12.182 --> 1:04:14.684
Well, well, well, well,
well, well, well.

1:04:14.851 --> 1:04:17.645
Guess they ain't never gonna
stop talking about that.

1:04:17.645 --> 1:04:19.397
Talking about what?

1:04:19.397 --> 1:04:22.275
That ... that dang fool barmaid,
that Mary what's-her-name.

1:04:23.401 --> 1:04:26.613
Don't they know they ain't never
gonna find that girl now?

1:04:26.613 --> 1:04:29.449
Missing like that for that long,
they ought to know better.

1:04:30.784 --> 1:04:33.620
- She ain't missing.
- You got a theory, too.

1:04:34.621 --> 1:04:36.331
She ain't missing.

1:04:36.498 --> 1:04:38.666
- I got her.
- You got her?

1:04:38.666 --> 1:04:39.959
I got her.

1:04:39.959 --> 1:04:41.544
Ez, what do you mean,
you got her?

1:04:42.670 --> 1:04:44.047
Out at my place.

1:04:44.672 --> 1:04:47.634
Mama, Miss Johnson,
a lot of others, too.

1:04:47.634 --> 1:04:49.427
Ez, you cut out that kind of talk!

1:04:52.472 --> 1:04:54.474
I just didn't want you
to worry about her, that's all.

1:04:54.641 --> 1:04:55.975
I ain't worried about her.

1:04:57.727 --> 1:05:00.313
Besides that, there wouldn't be
nothing to worry about anyway

1:05:00.480 --> 1:05:02.315
if you had her,
that's for dang sure.

1:05:02.732 --> 1:05:04.984
You wouldn't know what to do with her
if she sat right down in your lap.

1:05:05.527 --> 1:05:07.362
Now, Ez, you cutout
that crazy talk.

1:05:07.904 --> 1:05:10.740
- I was only joking.
- It ain't very funny.

1:05:10.740 --> 1:05:13.118
You're gonna get yourself
locked up in the poky.

1:05:13.284 --> 1:05:15.078
Hello, Dad. I'm home.

1:05:16.287 --> 1:05:18.748
- Hi there, son. Afternoon, Sally.
- Hi, Mr Kootz.

1:05:18.957 --> 1:05:20.750
Hello, Ezra.
Do you know Sally?

1:05:21.376 --> 1:05:24.587
No, sir, sure don't.
Hello, Sally.

1:05:24.921 --> 1:05:27.215
- Hi.
- Listen, I'll be back in a minute.

1:05:27.382 --> 1:05:29.592
Sally here works down
at Anderson's hardware store.

1:05:29.592 --> 1:05:32.429
Gonna slip us a few free shells,
ain't you, Sally, huh?

1:05:32.429 --> 1:05:33.972
No, sir. I can't do that.

1:05:34.180 --> 1:05:36.516
You can sure give us
a little discount, can't you?

1:05:36.724 --> 1:05:40.520
- Sorry, I can't do that, either.
- Well, what am I gonna do?

1:05:40.812 --> 1:05:42.647
I mean, hunting season
starts next week.

1:05:42.897 --> 1:05:44.441
Ez, what am I gonna do?

1:05:44.441 --> 1:05:47.777
I gotta buy myself some shells,
I gotta get some traps,

1:05:47.777 --> 1:05:49.863
gotta get a whole bunch of gear.

1:05:49.863 --> 1:05:52.490
Actually, I wish they didn't sell
that stuff down there.

1:05:52.657 --> 1:05:53.992
I really don't like it.

1:05:54.284 --> 1:05:55.743
How come you don't like it?

1:05:56.453 --> 1:06:00.415
Well, you know, I just don't like
the idea of shooting animals

1:06:00.665 --> 1:06:01.958
and trapping them and...

1:06:02.125 --> 1:06:04.544
Aw, Sally's soft-hearted.

1:06:05.628 --> 1:06:09.674
- Aw, so is Ezra. Ain't you, Ez, huh?
- Yes, sir.

1:06:09.674 --> 1:06:12.844
You know, honey, if we didn't shoot 'em,
they'd just starve to death.

1:06:12.844 --> 1:06:14.596
Got to keep that balance,
you know?

1:06:14.596 --> 1:06:17.015
Don't you worry about them deer, Sally.
They don't feel nothing.

1:06:17.015 --> 1:06:18.725
I'll never believe that.

1:06:18.892 --> 1:06:20.977
Come on, Sal.
Let's get going.

1:06:21.144 --> 1:06:23.396
- OK, Mr Kootz.
- Bye, Sal. See you later, son.

1:06:23.396 --> 1:06:25.273
- See you, Dad.
- Bye.

1:06:56.346 --> 1:06:58.515
- Good day, Ezra.
- Hello, Ezra.

1:06:59.849 --> 1:07:01.226
Coming hunting with us today, Ez?

1:07:03.019 --> 1:07:04.479
Oh, no, I'm...

1:07:04.938 --> 1:07:06.773
I'm just gonna get
some antifreeze.

1:07:06.981 --> 1:07:09.317
We'll all need some
if we keep standing around out here.

1:07:13.696 --> 1:07:15.740
- Morning, Sally.
- Oh, good morning.

1:07:29.379 --> 1:07:32.465
Do I get my change,
or do I have to pay for that, too?

1:07:32.799 --> 1:07:36.135
I'm sorry. Thank you.

1:07:38.888 --> 1:07:40.306
Why did you do that, Brad?

1:07:42.183 --> 1:07:45.937
That is a beauty.
Hey, Ez, come over here. Have a look.

1:07:48.273 --> 1:07:51.651
Is that a beauty
or is that a beauty?

1:07:56.114 --> 1:07:57.657
Pow!

1:08:00.034 --> 1:08:02.453
Oh, Ez.

1:08:02.453 --> 1:08:04.539
You feel that.

1:08:04.747 --> 1:08:07.083
You just snuggle up to that, Ez.

1:08:14.841 --> 1:08:18.803
A fella could hit just about anything
that moves with that, wouldn't he?

1:08:26.853 --> 1:08:27.854
Yep.

1:08:29.606 --> 1:08:30.732
It's nice, all right.

1:08:32.233 --> 1:08:34.569
That's sure got to be
an understatement, I guess.

1:08:35.111 --> 1:08:37.864
The only thing wrong with you is
you don't know nothing about guns.

1:08:38.031 --> 1:08:40.074
'Cause if you did,
you'd sure see

1:08:40.074 --> 1:08:42.869
what a beautiful piece of work
this here thing is.

1:08:42.869 --> 1:08:45.246
Yes siree, it sure is that.

1:08:46.914 --> 1:08:48.249
Oh, yeah.

1:08:49.500 --> 1:08:52.295
Well, me and Brad better get
the hell out of here

1:08:52.295 --> 1:08:54.422
or all them damn deer
will be gone to Florida.

1:08:56.841 --> 1:08:59.218
- OK, will you stick those on the bill, Sal?
- Fine.

1:08:59.218 --> 1:09:00.887
- You got everything you need, son?
- Yeah.

1:09:00.887 --> 1:09:03.389
- Hey, Ez?
- Huh?

1:09:03.765 --> 1:09:05.099
You sure you won't come
with us now?

1:09:05.767 --> 1:09:08.144
- Where you going?
- Up east Old Landridge Road.

1:09:08.686 --> 1:09:09.979
Oh. No, thanks.

1:09:11.272 --> 1:09:12.815
Always had good luck
up there, Ez.

1:09:14.233 --> 1:09:15.526
No, I don't like that stuff.

1:09:17.862 --> 1:09:19.530
OK. So long.

1:09:19.530 --> 1:09:21.616
We'll be back later
to fill up the thermos.

1:09:21.616 --> 1:09:23.576
- See you later.
- All right. Bye-bye.

1:09:31.876 --> 1:09:35.505
Um, just the antifreeze?
Would you like anything else, Ezra?

1:09:44.347 --> 1:09:47.266
I was gonna look around.

1:09:47.642 --> 1:09:55.642
Oh, that's fine. Take your time.

1:11:52.975 --> 1:11:54.644
What are you doing, Ez?

1:12:52.660 --> 1:13:00.660
Stop.

1:14:07.234 --> 1:14:08.444
Brad!

1:14:08.444 --> 1:14:10.571
Brad, help me, please!

1:14:13.991 --> 1:14:16.577
Brad! Brad!

1:14:20.122 --> 1:14:22.458
Brad, help me.

1:14:22.667 --> 1:14:32.926
Brad.

1:14:32.927 --> 1:14:40.927
Brad, help.

1:16:57.696 --> 1:16:59.323
No!

1:17:00.241 --> 1:17:01.575
Help!

1:17:02.827 --> 1:17:05.079
No! No!

1:17:06.872 --> 1:17:09.625
Oh, no. Please, no.

1:17:11.252 --> 1:17:14.046
Please. Please, no.

1:18:00.968 --> 1:18:03.345
Hey,Dad!
Dad, come in here quick!

1:18:33.334 --> 1:18:34.627
We bought some stuff

1:18:34.793 --> 1:18:36.837
and then we went out
to the Old Landridge Road.

1:18:37.004 --> 1:18:42.051
Well, according to the register,
you and he were her last customers.

1:18:42.343 --> 1:18:44.094
- Us?
- Mm-hmm.

1:18:44.595 --> 1:18:46.430
- Ezra bought some antifreeze.
- Yeah!

1:18:46.639 --> 1:18:48.807
- Said he was gonna take it out to his...
- Who, Ezra Cobb?

1:18:49.016 --> 1:18:50.434
He was still here when we left.

1:18:50.643 --> 1:18:52.102
Daddy, I'll bet he did something.

1:18:52.311 --> 1:18:54.563
- I'll bet he did.
- Who, Ez? He wouldn't.

1:18:54.563 --> 1:18:58.317
- You know Ez wouldn't do nothing like this.
- He's crazy enough to do anything.

1:18:58.484 --> 1:19:01.070
I've known Ez for 25 years,
and I tell you, he could not do a thing...

1:19:01.278 --> 1:19:04.073
Suppose we all go out
to his place and take a look?

1:19:04.240 --> 1:19:06.784
- Yeah, let's go.
- Come on.

1:20:07.219 --> 1:20:08.512
Ezra!

1:20:09.013 --> 1:20:10.264
'Ezra!'

1:20:15.644 --> 1:20:18.897
The wages of sin is death.

1:20:22.985 --> 1:20:26.280
Do you know what God done then,
don't you, boy?

1:20:33.912 --> 1:20:35.581
He burned 'em in hell!

1:20:36.248 --> 1:20:38.792
Death! Death! Death!

1:20:40.919 --> 1:20:47.384
Oh, no!

1:21:24.630 --> 1:21:29.510
♪ Vengeance within demanding ♪

1:21:31.011 --> 1:21:35.974
♪ I Whose is the voice I hear? ♪

1:21:37.309 --> 1:21:43.232
♪ I Sweetly, the songs are calling ♪

1:21:44.274 --> 1:21:49.780
♪ I Open the door for me I ♪

1:22:16.974 --> 1:22:18.976
'Several nights later,
a group of townspeople,

1:22:19.143 --> 1:22:22.855
'reportedly led by Harlan Kootz,
under cover of night,

1:22:23.522 --> 1:22:27.401
'burned the Cobb farm
to the ground.'
